10/01/2011
ANKARA, Turkey -- A Turkish engineer who was kidnapped in Afghanistan last year has been released, Foreign Minister Ahmet Davutoglu confirmed on Sunday (January 9th). 
According to local media, Coskun Caloglu, who was kidnapped in May or June in the southwestern province of Nimroz, has been released as a result of negotiations led by the Turkish Embassy in Kabul. 
Kidnappings are common in Afghanistan, usually by the Taliban or criminal groups seeking ransom. 
(Anadolu news agency, AFP, AP, NTV - 09/01/11)
